<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: POLLUTION RESEARCH SELLS 9% STAKE TO L. A. INVESTOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pollution Research &amp; Control Corp., a Glendale maker of 
pollution-monitoring equipment, said it raised $160,000 by selling a 9% stake 
in the company to Los Angeles investor Lee Sion. 
</P>
<P>
In a filing with the federal Securities and Exchange Commission, Pollution 
Research said it sold 400,000 shares of its common stock to Sion for 40 cents 
each. The company also granted Sion a three-year option to buy an additional 
200,000 shares at an exercise price of 40 cents a share. 
</P>
