REGIONAL EARNINGS: SEMTECH REPORTS LOSS OF $152,000 IN 3RD QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Semtech Corp., a Newbury Park maker of rectifiers and other electronic 
components, reported a $152,000 loss for its fiscal third quarter, contrasted 
with a $251,000 profit a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
The loss in the quarter that ended Oct. 28 came despite a 12% increase in 
revenue, to $5.47 million from $4.90 million. The loss partly reflected a 
$300,000 charge that Semtech incurred during the quarter in connection with 
closure of a subsidiary. 
</P>
<P>
For the first nine months of its fiscal year, Semtech's net income fell to 
$40,000 from $830,000 a year earlier, and its nine-month revenue edged up to 
$14.8 million from $14.6 million. 
