<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: BASEBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Bob Welch's new contract with the Oakland Athletics is worth $13.8 million over 
four years, making him the second-best-paid pitcher in baseball behind teammate 
Dave Stewart. 
</P>
<P>
Welch will get a $2.2-million signing bonus and yearly salaries of $2.9 
million, sources familiar with the deal said. The average annual value of $3.45 
million is the ninth-best in baseball. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
