<P>
Date for New GATT Talks Set: To try to revive trade talks that collapsed this 
month, the head of the governing body on world trade called on negotiators to 
return to the bargaining table Jan. 15. The session was called by Arthur 
Dunkel, director-general of the General Agreement on Tariffs and Trade. There 
has been no sign that the positions among GATT nations have changed enough -- 
especially in the key area of farm subsidies -- to salvage efforts to 
liberalize global trade. 
</P>
