<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COSTA MESA; 
</P>
<P>
DEADLINE TO APPLY FOR GRANTS IS JAN. 18 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nonprofit organizations have until Jan. 18 to apply for city grants to pay for 
the advertising and promotional costs of their community-related activities. 
</P>
<P>
Organizations must be nonprofit corporations or unincorporated associations and 
must provide proof of nonprofit status. 
</P>
<P>
To qualify for funding, applications must show that the organization holds 
activities that benefit the city and its residents, enhance the image of the 
city, exhibit civic pride and serve a charitable, philanthropic, cultural or 
educational purpose. 
</P>
<P>
The organizations must be based in Costa Mesa and cannot have received funds 
from other city grant programs in the same fiscal year. 
</P>
<P>
Application forms are available at the city manager's office on the fifth floor 
of City Hall, 77 Fair Drive. The office also will mail out applications. 
</P>
<P>
Applications are due by 5 p.m. Jan. 18. They will be reviewed in early 
February, and grants will be awarded in late February or early March. 
</P>
<P>
For information, call (714) 754-5327. 
</P>
</TEXT>
