<HEADLINE>
<P>
LA VALLEY HITS BOARDS TO BEAT SADDLEBACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles Valley College dominated Saddleback on the boards and won, 67-51, 
in the first round of the Riverside women's basketball tournament Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Tisa Rush had 15 points and nine rebounds and Wendy Bruse added 12 points and 
13 rebounds as LA Valley (11-1) outrebounded the Gauchos by 19. LA Valley had 
four players with at least 10 rebounds each. 
</P>
<P>
Erin Schimeneck had 14 points and seven rebounds and Kristen Okura had seven 
points and 12 rebounds for Saddleback (8-3), which had its six-game winning 
streak ended. 
</P>
