<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
RESERVES LEAD SCC OVER OCCIDENTAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fueled by 42 points from its reserves, the Southern California College men's 
basketball team defeated Occidental, 99-81, Monday in a nonconference game at 
SCC. 
</P>
<P>
Occidental made all six of its three-point shots in the first half and trailed, 
50-40, at the half. 
</P>
<P>
The Tigers, who made 10 of 16 three-point attempts, then closed to within two 
points with about 17 minutes remaining before the Vanguards pulled away. 
</P>
<P>
Jeff Bickmore scored 16 points and Mike Henjum and Bryan Moore each had 13 for 
the Vanguards (10-2), who shot 57% from the field in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
Rod Leinbach, who made five of six three-point shots, scored 19 to lead 
Occidental. Everette Hill and Brett Dennis each added 15 for the Tigers. 
</P>
<P>
Pacific Christian 96, Loma Linda 78 -- Kenny Crawford had 29 points and 14 
rebounds, Mike Vincent had 23 points and 11 rebounds and Kenny Kao had 21 
points for Pacific Christian (11-7) at Cal State Fullerton's Titan Gym. Loma 
Linda is 1-8. 
</P>
<P>
In a California Coastal Conference women's basketball game: 
</P>
<P>
Pacific Christian 65, Loma Linda 38 -- Donna Allen had 15 points for host PCC 
(5-6). 
</P>
</TEXT>
