<P>
HALF-DAY OFF FOR U.S. EMPLOYEES CHRISTMAS EVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Bush today gave all federal employees a half-day off on Monday, 
Christmas Eve. 
</P>
<P>
His order closes all federal departments and agencies early on Dec. 24, but 
allows department heads to require certain workers or offices to work a full 
day if needed "for reasons of national security or defense or for other 
essential public reasons." 
</P>
<P>
The order did not specify a quitting time, but most offices are likely to close 
around noon, local time. 
</P>
<P>
The order does not affect state or local government employees. 
</P>
